trans-unit.source: Represents an unsigned rights managed <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"></xref> or an unsigned <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"></xref> template.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en usignert rettigheter administrert <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"> </xref> eller usignerte <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"> </xref> mal.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> defines security data about rights, users, and other security-related information.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>definerer sikkerhetsdata om rettigheter, brukerne og andre sikkerhetsrelaterte informasjon.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: The license defines how a specific user on a specific computer can use specified rights-managed content.
trans-unit.target: Lisensen definerer hvordan en bestemt bruker på en bestemt datamaskin kan bruke angitte innhold som behandles av rettigheter.

trans-unit.source: The publishing process begins with the document author, who defines rights information in an UnsignedPublishLicense.
trans-unit.target: Publisering prosessen begynner med forfatteren av dokumentet, som definerer informasjon om brukerrettigheter i en UnsignedPublishLicense.

trans-unit.source: Next, the authoring application calls the UnsignedPublishLicense.<xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A> method to create a signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>.
trans-unit.target: Neste kaller redigeringsprogrammet UnsignedPublishLicense. <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A>metoden til å opprette en signert <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A>

trans-unit.source: The signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> can then be provided to the end-user client application which can call <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A> to request an end-user <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>.
trans-unit.target: Den signerte <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>kan angis til sluttbrukeren klientprogrammet som kan ringe <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A>å be om en sluttbruker <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: The returned <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense> then allows the client application to exercise the rights that are granted to the user.
trans-unit.target: Det returnerte <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>tillater klientprogram Vær rettigheter som er gitt til brukeren.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>

trans-unit.source: The document author can use the UnsignedPublishLicense class either to create a signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>, or to build and serialize a <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> template.
trans-unit.target: Forfatteren av dokumentet kan klassen UnsignedPublishLicense enten bruke til å opprette en signert <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>, eller til å bygge og serialisere en <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>malen.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: As with other <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement> types, UnsignedPublishLicense is only usable in full trust applications.
trans-unit.target: Som med andre <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement>typer UnsignedPublishLicense brukes bare i fullstendig klarering programmer.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement>
